# batlleship

About:
Project consisits of the following folders and documents: docs, src,  Doxyfile and makefile. In folder docs one can find all the documantation that is needed for this project (devspec, fspec, prd). Folder src contains main source code of the project.

Short manual:
After downloading the project open terminal, and enter "make" command. There will be created folders bin and obj. Directory obj will contain object files. Directory bin will contain an executable file named 'run'. Now run the executable file. Game will start. After finishing placement 4 ships the computer you must enter the coordinates of the field. You must guess all the fields where can be ships. Destroy them. The game will be over if there is no ships in the sea. In command line enter "make doxygen" and doxygen documentation will be created in docs folder. Besides, in battleship folder you can run "make clean" command which will delete bin, obj, Doxygen folders.

The game:
This project is a game called Battliship which is written in C++. The user must play with computer. 
The game implements several basic features: 
1) Creates the sea: 10x10 matrix in dynamic memory. 
2) The program randomly generates coordinates, destinations, sizes of the ships and sets the ships in the sea.
3) Providing a simple parameters based way of firing shoots for the console application.
The game will end when all ships will be destroyed. 
